http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/TTD-plans-Veda-Parayanam-during-Pournami-Garuda-Seva/article13995452.ece

The Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanams (TTD) has announced to conduct ‘Visesha Veda Parayanam’, with over 1,500 parayanamdars registered under the Veda Parayana scheme, during the auspicious occasion of Pournami Garuda Seva in Tirumala on January 24.TTD Executive Officer D. Sambasiva Rao on Monday instructed the officials concerned to come up with an effective action plan to execute the programme.He further instructed the SVBC officials to make the programmes during Sankranthi more appealing, aimed at a wider audience across the globe, particularly the ‘Go Puja’ planned in Andhra Pradesh and Telangana.Mr. Rao also directed engineering officials to complete pending works in accommodation centres.